solution.p:
The car's speed increases with time. So its highest speed on any time interval occurs at the right hand end of the interval and the best possible upper estimate for the distance traveled is given by the right Riemann sum with \Delta x =0.5, which is
\big[v(0.5)+v(1.0)+v(1.5)+v(2.0)\big]\times 0.5 &=\big[14+22+30+40\big]\times 0.5
&= 53\text{ m}

